1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Taking walks and playing games when there's sunny weather

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
How to cure a tree

7
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Just a polar bear on a stroll

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Bucky! Bucky, hey! You in there?

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
We're going to the river, right?

10
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Have those wires always been there?

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Where are you? Come on, Bucky!

12
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
I'm sorry, Bjorn! I can't go today!

13
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Where are you?

14
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
What do you think you're doing?

15
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Stop that this instant! I mean it! Bucky!

16
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Oh!

17
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Ouchie McPainPain! Why are you screaming?

18
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
You totally made me hurt myself!

19
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
You say you're hurt, huh?

20
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,000
What about the tree?

21
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:28,000
What? The apple tree? Like, what about it? It's only a tree, right?

22
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
A tree is a living thing!

23
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
It feels pain too, you know!

24
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Why are you torturing it?

25
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Me? Torturing? How?

26
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,000
There's been no torture! I'm setting up the internet, dude!

27
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Can you just imagine the entire world at our fingertips?

28
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,000
All the latest information in the entire world!

29
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
And it's mine for the browsing!

30
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Uh, you're hurting the tree for the sake of internet, huh?

31
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,000
What happens if the tree dies?

32
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:04,000
This is only a tree, Bjorn! We have a forest full of them, see? What's your problem?

33
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Just watch! When I am through, I'll show you the whole wide world! So be able to see what our forest looks like from space!

34
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:20,000
I don't want to see a tree suffer like this! Not even from space!

35
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:24,000
You've hurt the poor thing, and now it feels bad!

36
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Bjorn, you are one odd bear! I'm attempting to drag you into the current millennium!

37
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:33,000
All that you seem to be concerned with are some silly trees!

38
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:38,000
I'm not interested in the kind of progress that causes any trees to suffer!

39
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
You can do your internetting without me!

40
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Why was Bjorn that upset? I've just made this forest so much cooler! By far!

41
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
It's really working!

42
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:53,000
I'm a genius! They should call me Albert Einstein!

43
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Home sweet home!

44
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Whoa! Bjorn sweet Bjorn! What's he doing?

45
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Poor thing!

46
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Hello Bjorn! Are you alright? Are you still mad at me?

47
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
I'm not mad Bucky! Just-

48
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,000
But you have a growl face!

49
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Well, I'm worried about this poor apple tree!

50
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:19,000
I've given it a lot of water, but it's still not looking any better!

51
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:23,000
So why not just find the right way to fix the tree?

52
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:27,000
You're an expert on branches and leaves and dirt and all that stuff!

53
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Bjorn, I'll help in any way that I can! Just let me know what to do! I'm pretty darn good at everything!

54
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Listen, you don't understand! The apple tree is a living thing! It can't just be repaired! It needs to be treated so that it can heal! But I don't know what to do!

55
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:54,000
So, you need to heal a tree, but you're not certain how!

56
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:06,000
When there's something that you need to learn, you just have to ask! And you know where you can find out the answer to pretty much any question? Wait for it! On the internet!

57
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:10,000
There! It's really easy! See? Eureka!

58
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Ladder time! Yeah!

59
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Get these out of your way! And tape! Yeah!

60
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Catch! Nailed it!

61
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Oh yeah!

62
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Incoming!

63
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Looking good!

64
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
Alright!

65
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Nice work!

66
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Thanks!

67
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
It looks so much better than before, right?

68
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
It will heal in no time!

69
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,000
What a relief!

70
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,000
What did I tell you, Bjorn?

71
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,000
What would we have done if we hadn't had the internet?

72
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:05,000
You must see now! It's wonderful! The way that scientific progress can improve our lives!

73
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,000
You're right!

74
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:13,000
But from now on, can we progress without causing harm to the living things around us?

75
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Like trees, or flowers, or ferns?

76
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Let's just not harm nature at all! Ever! Period!

77
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Or else, we won't have anything nice to look at from space!

78
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,000
You look very handsome from space, by the way!

79
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,000
By the way!

80
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
By the way!

